&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;X3 Full Time Permanent Posts&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;X1 Full Time, Fixed Term Post for 12 months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking to recruit highly motivated Health Visitors to work in our 0-19 Integrated Public Health Nursing Service which is responsible for delivering the Healthy Child Programme and targeted interventions and is committed to improving outcomes for Children, Young People and families in Hull.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the day to day management of a 0-11 year’s caseload including universal, universal partnership, universal partnership plus and enhanced family pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to develop excellent partnership working relationships in order to provide seamless services to Children, Young people and their families and to meet national and local public health priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as a valued member of our integrated team the post holder will need to demonstrate safe, effective and caring evidence-based practice, possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills with a commitment to team working. You must be willing to undertake a range of leadership and mentoring responsibilities and support organisational changes.&lt;/p&gt;
